const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Will Google penalize my site for AI-generated content?",
    a: "Google's own guidelines are explicit: quality and usefulness matter, not how content was produced. Every article Stacc publishes is keyword-researched, SEO-optimized, and written to answer real questions your customers ask. Our customers have published over 4 million words without a single manual action or ranking penalty. The content works because it's built for humans first. Not to game an algorithm.",
  },
  {
    q: "Why is it only $99? What's the catch?",
    a: "No catch. Agencies charge $3,500/month because they employ account managers, writers, editors, and strategists. We automated every one of those steps. Keyword research, writing, SEO scoring, internal linking, and publishing. You pay $99 because there's no $3,100 team behind your account. There's a system that does the same work in seconds, consistently, every month.",
  },
  {
    q: "How long until I see results?",
    a: "Most customers see meaningful ranking improvements within 60–90 days. The real question is: what happens in 6 months if you don't start now? Your competitor who started today will have 180 published, indexed articles. You'll still be on page 3 wondering why they get all the calls. SEO is a compounding asset. The earlier you start, the bigger the lead you build.",
  },
  {
    q: "How is this different from just using ChatGPT?",
    a: "ChatGPT writes content. Stacc ranks it. The difference is the complete set of SEO content tools sitting on top: keyword research calibrated to your specific market, optimization scoring that grades every article before it publishes, internal linking across your site, meta tags, schema markup, and direct CMS integration. ChatGPT gives you a draft you have to manually optimize and upload. Stacc gives you a live, ranking page.",
  },
  {
    q: "What if the content doesn't sound like my business?",
    a: "During setup, Stacc reads your existing website and analyzes your tone, audience, and service language. In the first batch, 94% of customers say the articles sound like them or better. For the other 6%, two tweaks to the style settings fix it. You can review every article before it publishes. Most customers stop reviewing after the first month because they trust what they're seeing.",
  },
  {
    q: "What if I cancel. Do I lose my content?",
